<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="385" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="106.[1456,2661,1477,2176]" pageId="106" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1456,1689,1949,1978]" pageId="106" pageNumber="385">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Puebla Deermouse is presumably nocturnal, and given its exceptionally long tail, it is probably arboreal.
</paragraph>
